<subSubSection pageId="471" pageNumber="472" type="diversity">
<paragraph pageId="471" pageNumber="472">Diversity.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="471" pageNumber="472">
Worldwide, with about 735 species in 47 genera. These genera are placed in five tribes: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1853" lsidName="" pageId="471" pageNumber="472" rank="tribe" tribe="Metriini">Metriini</taxonomicName>
(three species), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Horn" authorityYear="1881" lsidName="" pageId="471" pageNumber="472" rank="tribe" tribe="Mystropomini">Mystropomini</taxonomicName>
(two species in the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chaudoir" authorityYear="1848" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Mystropomus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="471" pageNumber="472" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="471" pageNumber="472">Mystropomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hope" authorityYear="1838" lsidName="" pageId="471" pageNumber="472" rank="tribe" tribe="Ozaenini">Ozaenini</taxonomicName>
(about 180 species), 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="471" pageNumber="472" rank="tribe" tribe="Paussini">Paussini</taxonomicName>
(about 560 species), and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gestro" authorityYear="1892" lsidName="" pageId="471" pageNumber="472" rank="tribe" tribe="Protopaussini">Protopaussini</taxonomicName>
(eight species in the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gestro" authorityYear="1892" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Protopaussus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="471" pageNumber="472" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="471" pageNumber="472">Protopaussus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Gestro). The Northern Hemisphere fauna is represented by about 70 species (roughly 9.5% of the world fauna) and North America by only seven species (less than 1% of the world fauna).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
